Mr. Reid really listens to each students questions and answers ALL questions without making them feel stupid--even if it is something that "we should already know". He is EXCELLENT at explaining things in a way that everyone understands. It is easy to tell that he CARES about his students and their success in the class. and he's attractive too!
Excellent at explaining concepts. Great lectures!

I'm taking beginning stage combat with him this semester and it is so much fun! Matthew is  a fun professor who knows what he is teaching and is willing to take his time with the students. We just moved onto rapiers, but he was very helpful during unarmed combat. One of the most fun classes I have ever taken!
Please do not rate here, the name is wrong, go to Lindsay.

I've already taken TMA 201 with Lindsey and I am currently in 202. She loves what she teaches and knows practically everything. This class has a ton of reading and assignments but it's very interesting! These classes also count as a GE.
great teacher and always made sure all the students understood everything before moving on.
Hilarious professor. I felt like I actually learned more with the half term class then the ITAL101 that I took for a full semester. He is sassy and makes fun of everyone including himself.

Adrian is great. He is genuinely interested in the success of his students and makes a real effort to help them understand and progress. He's not a pushover, but he's understanding and willing to work with students if they put in effort. He's an engaging speaker and fair grader. I'd take his class again!

Adrian is such a great Italian professor, and just teacher in general! I went in expecting the class to be a lot more work and a lot harder than it was! The way he teaches makes you feel like you're hardly doing any work while actually learning a ton! He's really funny and genuine and just easy to talk to and get help from.

Adrian, Adrian, Adrian, where do start? Firstly, he insists you call him Dr. Ramjoué, which is weird because although he does have a Ph.D in sanitation disaster management, he has no degree in Italian. Weird! Anyway, he is still an awesome teacher, even if the vocab he teaches you is very scatological. Also, he always smells good. Like REALLY good.

Dr. Ramjoue's class has been one of my favorites this semester. He expects a lot, but is always willing to help. Italian doesn't come easily to me, but listening to the soothing sounds of his voice really helped me get into the swing of things.

Professor Ramjoue was a really fun teacher. He tries really hard to be efficient and teach clearly but he isn't scared to be a bit sarcastic and have fun with the students. He is really nice and willing to work with you as long as you put for the effort that it takes to learn another language.

Dr. Wilkinson really wants his  students to succeed! You work with your group one day a week and then learn as a class the other day. I only spent about an hour outside of class per week on homework. The whole-class instruction days can get a little boring, but overall I learned a lot in this class and was spiritually inspired by Dr. Wilkinson.

He was an amazing teacher. He makes sure you get an A in the class. His course is really organized and I know what to expect every week. Also his TA's are really helpful and let you know how to get an A. This class was truly inspirational.
Mrs. Malloy is an amazing teacher. Math 302 is a very hard class and you should be prepared to work hard; however, Mrs. Malloy really cares about her students and wants them to do well in the class
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--Amazing lectures

comment: Happy to help students comes to her office hours and really does a good job of helping me understand.
Not an intense math professor. Willing to listen and agreeable.
She absolutely loves math and prepares well for class. Always willing to be fair on tough assignments. Even works out tough problems in class.
She is always well prepared to teach. She doesn't grade the homework herself but her grader is very nit picky,  you can get the right answer but lose all point due to your "math grammar"
It is a hard class, but she is always willing to help

Professor Malloy is very nice and definitely willing to help if you go in during her hours. However she is the hardest grader I have ever had and looks for excuses to take points off. She treats homework like it is an exam and is not clear about what needs to change. I believe she is one of the professors who wants a very low average for her class.
Professor Malloy is very nitpicky when it comes to grading. Her lectures are vague and dry. There were problems on the test that she didn't prepare us for.
Didn't find teaching style helpful. Didn't teach clear at all. Constantly makes you guess what she is thinking, never tells you if you are right or wrong.

Professor Herfort is an amazing math professor. He cares about his students. Math 313 is not an easy class, but if you take it with him, you will understand all the concepts. Practice tests are similar like the midterms. I will take all my math classes with him but unfortunately he is leaving the country :(

Dr. Herfort is hilarious; if you've never heard anyone ask for more questions in Portuguese with an Austrian accent, he's your guy. His accent can be difficult at first, but you get used to it. Very clear about what proofs will be on the test; practice tests prepare you well for actual tests. He knows applications of Linear, but does not force them
He's a solidly good teacher.  He's Austrian, so he has an accent.  Tests are proportional to the difficulty of the class, and homework isn't too bad.  It's a good class with a good teacher.

Mr. Herfort is a kind-hearted guy. He wants to help out his students and you can tell by his attitude. English is not his first language so initially I had a hard time following him but I got used to his accent quickly. He thinks and works quickly but he always makes sure everyone is on board. He's not easy but I recommend taking his class.
